item.title: This wasn’t technology.This was sacrifice.
item.description: We burned CDs. In the early 2000s. With a Discman that skipped if you breathed too loudly. Your favorite song always glitching at the exact same spot — but you listened anyway, because it was your favorite. Car stereos worth more than the actual car. A freshly burned CD for the weekend, carefully labeled with a Sharpie and way too many feelings. We infected the family PC with at least three viruses just to download the hottest tracks from LimeWire. The computer was never the same again, but it was worth it.

item.title: PTGDump: Memes I Send My Wife Vol. X
item.description:
Hello Everyone!
I don't see this as a problem.
"Like, ALL of it."
Let's knife fight about it.
I'm so sorry.
I play to tie.
She knows who she married.
Accurate
Men only want one thing.
I'm not great at cocktail parties. Small talk infuriates me, and I'm only good at it when I am showing open disdain for my surroundings.
See? It helps!
She married me knowing full well how many bad puns would be in her life.
"I've had ALL of it."
I guess I really don't get this one. My wife is ways down for whatever I want to do, Father's day or not. We don't have all the same interests, but we give each other room to pursue them, and share in them often.
(Some) women really *do* want a weird little goblin man. As long as that goblin man is mostly responsible and acts as a true partner in the felationship.
STAND BACK
Literally said this to my wife yesterday as she enjoyed a chia pudding snack (which was super gross to me. It was the texture)
*gentle gasp* dat booty
It works, fellas (and fellow penis-havers)!
We started off long-distance, and she would always nick one of my shirts to keep when I had to leave. When a girl gets your scent, it's serious.
Hope someone give you a kiss today.
*Ted Lasso voice* "I appreciate ya."
Nyoooom!
She is the itchiest woman in the world.
Delicious, yes?
Everyone must enjoy this modern Rice
"Braaughflflflflf"
A man needs a moment, ok?
Again. Puns.
Thanks for reading! MV Edit: Y'all are the best. Thanks for the accolades. Send pics of dogs in silly hats. I also tried to plug my YT channel on the last dump, but I think Business Daddy didn't like the external URL in the descriptions. But check my profile, or just search my name on YT and say hi! I like it when people say hi.

item.description: My old boss made a deal with me to take care of the yard in exchange for living here. It's a farm.... he sold some land and is leasing the rest. He's keeping ownership of the houses and buildings. He's basically retiring. I don't like the other guy that is leasing the land and taking ownership of the equipment, so I won't be working for him. My part time job working on a (new) ranch is going to be my new full time job, but a year out at best until I get full time wages. I've also reached out to neighbors and friends for extra part time work or contracts, and they're all cool with giving me some work. I don't have any debt or kids, so I'll be OK. :)
